{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SKjiDV3XNvvkRjizCfmQBS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: deterministic-service-test\n     3→description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `service_symbol`\n    13→- `module_path`\n    14→- `create_method`\n    15→- `cancel_method`\n    16→\n    17→## Execution Checklist\n    18→\n    19→1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20→2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21→3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22→4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23→5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24→\n    25→## Guardrails\n    26→\n    27→- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28→- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29→- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4248ef77-8e8b-477c-a0f7-0cfe0438fbb0","uuid":"302c406b-f3c5-4054-95ef-7ef31bb8efba"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KRTfaSHwxRdKjCRT6tg1yQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist/guidance document with no malicious content.\n\nHere is the deterministic-service-test checklist applied to your variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- `service_symbol`: CoreService\n- `module_path`: services.core_service\n- `create_method`: create_record\n- `cancel_method`: cancel_record\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n1. Use deterministic inputs — fix time, data, and randomness (e.g. freeze clock, static IDs) when testing `CoreService.create_record` / `cancel_record`.\n2. One behavior per test — e.g. `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_rejects_already_cancelled`.\n3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test between arrange and assert.\n4. Mock only external boundaries of `services.core_service` (DB/repo, clock, external clients) using `autospec=True`.\n5. Avoid shared mutable state — build fresh fixtures per test; no module-level mutables.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- Use pytest functions, not `unittest.TestCase`.\n- No real `datetime.now()` / `random` — inject or patch.\n- Assertions stay behavior-focused (returned value, state transition, boundary call), minimal in count.\n\nPer the Control Profile, I am not running `jig` and have only consulted the skill checklist."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":631,"cache_read_input_tokens":21638,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":631,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":466,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4248ef77-8e8b-477c-a0f7-0cfe0438fbb0","uuid":"e0c60a24-aaaf-4151-b299-89cf523d9e13"}
